&lt;h3 id="application"&gt;Application&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This concept can be used to implement a logging class by wrapping around an existing log library like the above print function and publish to an object like &lt;code&gt;std::ostringstream&lt;/code&gt; or directly to console.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="why-is-this-relevant"&gt;Why is this relevant?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the constructor or make_xxxxx() functions are called, the number of arguments vary based on the constructor
of the template class for which the smart pointer is instantiated.&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="misc"></category></entry></feed>